==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bivium
<hw>Biv"i*um</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a place
with two ways. See <er>Bivious</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One
side of an echinoderm, including a pair of ambulacra, in distinction
from the opposite side (<xex>trivium</xex>), which includes three
ambulacra.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bivouac</ent>⟦br⟧
